##Docker
to start a container with GPU access and port forwarding (for jupyter):

docker run -p 8888:8888 -ti --runtime=nvidia vision/deeplearning

+shared volume (-v)
docker run -it -p 8888:8888 -v /home/robinson/Documents/image-classification/dataset/train/:/tmp  --runtime=nvidia vision/deeplearning


##Usage
to start jupyter, use: juputer-notebook --ip 127.0.0.1 --allow-root

